      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEZA PUNK ROCKER NZ (1) has joined the powerhouse Jason Grimson stable since a last-start second in Adelaide and he was a Group 1 winner earlier in his career so he is capable. The ace draw gives him every chance to kick off for the new yard with a win. HES NO ROMEO NZ (8) backs up after a big effort to come from wider on this row to score by 13 metres on Tuesday. That was his second win in a row when attempting this distance here. Can settle just behind them and wait on the sprint lane. Could strike again. CATSEYE BEACH (7) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish second at this venue. Go well. Last-start winner FREE THINKER (9) is also in contention although the draw makes his job a bit tougher.",
